
Get a map at an address.
Regression test for the construction-time flag-redefined panic (PR #284):
name is REQUIRED and precedes address, which collides with the persistent
--address connection flag.

USAGE
  get-map-at-address <command>

ARGUMENT FLAGS
  --name     [R]  string  Required
  --address       string  Postal address — field name chosen to collide with the persistent --address connection flag and regression-test PR #284

CONNECTION FLAGS
  --address        string  Postal address — field name chosen to collide with the persistent --address connection flag and regression-test PR #284
  --force-trace    bool    Enable forced Google Cloud Trace header
  --insecure       bool    Make insecure connection (only on localhost)
  --token          string  Authenticate with a bearer token

OTHER FLAGS
  -f  --from-file    string  path to a JSON file containing the request payload
  -h  --help         bool    Show help for command
  -v  --verbose      bool    Enable verbose output
